findings.suggestion:
Add all items, then commit once outside the loop (and let the caller's transaction scope or an explicit try/except trigger session.rollback() on failure). For example:

    def bulk_create_items(session: Session, names: list[str]) -> list[Item]:
        items = [Item(name=name) for name in names]
        session.add_all(items)
        try:
            session.commit()
        except Exception:
            session.rollback()
            raise
        for item in items:
            session.refresh(item)
        return items

This makes the batch atomic and keeps retries idempotent at the transaction boundary.

